01:22:38.559 --> 01:22:41.959
But so that makes it good for this example, because we can do it very quickly here now

01:22:41.959 --> 01:22:42.959
together.

01:22:42.959 --> 01:22:49.359
So this is like a little bit of a toy example, but it can help you understand about embeddings.

01:22:49.359 --> 01:22:56.280
Because it's not, we cannot use every word in the world when we describe the cheeses.

01:22:56.280 --> 01:23:00.719
There's some small set of words, and also they aren't sentences.

01:23:00.719 --> 01:23:02.079
They're just like adjectives.

01:23:02.079 --> 01:23:03.079
Just adjectives.

01:23:03.120 --> 01:23:06.439
So think of it as like, we don't take all of natural language.

01:23:06.439 --> 01:23:10.319
We just take a subset, just a, just a little bit here.

01:23:10.319 --> 01:23:14.420
So this, so here, we're going to look at the flavor, the flavor.

01:23:14.420 --> 01:23:17.160
So here are five example flavors.

01:23:17.160 --> 01:23:18.959
So this is what our data looks like.

